body.name: naspaluro Ergonomic Office Chair, Mid Back Desk Chair with Adjustable Height, Swivel Chair with Flip-Up Arms and Lumbar Support, Breathable Mesh Computer Chair for Home/Study/Working, Blue
features: 【Ergonomic Computer Chair】Naspaluro office Chair adopts ergonomically designed S-shaped backrest, headrest and lumbar support, perfectly fit your body line and provide the best comfort for your back. The nylon wheels can rotate 360°freely and slide quietly on any type of floor.

【Multi-Adjustable Functions】5 humanized adjustment features to help you find the most comfortable sitting posture, allowing you to sit for a long time and stay relaxed. Adjustable armrests, lumbar support, headrest, seat height, and swing range, bring you a customized seating experience.

【Upgraded Quality Materials】Naspaluro Computer Chair is made of premium polyester mesh, high elasticity without deformation, more wear-resistant and breathable. The cushion is filled with high-density thick sponge, soft and durable, providing support while keeping it cool and sweat-free, make you comfortable and relaxed.

【Excellent Performance Standards】The height-adjusting GAS rod has passed SGS certification of Grade 3, more stable and safer. Heavy-duty base and nylon smooth rolling casters provide excellent stability and mobility. It also passed the push back test of 102kg and static pressure of 950kg.

【Easy to Assemble and Adjust】You can easily assemble the home desk chair by following the steps of the instructions. Pull up/down of the lever to adjust height of cushion; Pull in/out to lock backrest or turn on rocking mode, adjust the bottom knob to control the tightness of the backrest in rocking mode.

Not recommended to replace the wheels for use - the original factory configuration is the most suitable, please do not replace the wheels to avoid the problem of base breakage caused by the mismatch between the wheels and the base.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Naspaluro Ergonomic Office Chair: A Comfort Upgrade for My Home Workspace!
reviews.reviewText: I recently invested in the Naspaluro Ergonomic Office Chair for my home office, and let me tell you, it's been a total game-changer. As someone who spends long hours working at the desk, this chair has transformed my daily grind into a comfy and supportive experience.Pros:Ergonomic Bliss:This chair is a dream for my back. The ergonomic design gives me the right amount of lumbar support, making those long work sessions much more bearable. No more midday backaches – hallelujah!Adjustable Heights Galore:I love how I can tweak the height to my liking. Whether I'm sitting at the desk or need a quick break at a slightly higher or lower level, this chair's got my back – literally. It's like having a custom-made chair that fits me perfectly.Breathable Comfort:The mesh back is a game-changer, especially during the warmer months. It keeps me cool and comfy, preventing that dreaded sticky feeling you get with some chairs. It's the small details like this that make a big difference.Smooth Swivel Action:The 360-degree swivel is surprisingly satisfying. Need to grab something from the other side of the desk? No problem! The smooth rotation means no awkward stretching or shuffling around, and I can spin in my chair just for fun when I need a quick break.Sturdy and Stylish:This chair doesn’t just deliver on comfort; it looks good too. The sleek design adds a touch of modernity to my home office setup, and the sturdy build gives me confidence that it's not going to give out on me anytime soon.Cons:Assembly Challenge:Putting it together took a bit longer than expected. The instructions were clear, but it required a bit of patience. Once it was assembled, though, it was worth the effort.Armrests are Fixed:The armrests are fixed, so they don’t adjust up or down. While they're at a comfortable height for me, those who prefer customizable armrests might find this a bit limiting.In conclusion, the Naspaluro Ergonomic Office Chair is a gem for anyone looking to upgrade their home office comfort. It's not just a chair; it's a thoughtful investment in your well-being. The adjustable features, breathable design, and overall sturdiness make it a winner in my book. If you want to transform your workspace into a haven of comfort without breaking the bank, this chair is a fantastic choice. Highly recommended for anyone seeking an ergonomic chair that's both practical and stylish!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars for the girl bosses! excellent chair
reviews.reviewText: I highly recommend buying this chair! I work from home (yktv) and it's pretty light weight, comfortable and easy to assemble chair. It is also decently affordable and delivered to the right address (rural).I enjoy the fact that when rolled, it doesn't make much noise either. the Arm rests are comfortable on the skin and the back support is superb. One of the main reasons I requested a new office chair was the lack of support I had from my previous chair but this one does the trick! Also beautiful pink color but does get dirty right away. Can be cleaned with the shout to-go wipes or with dish soap. I've had it for about 2 months now and my back pain has been alleviated.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Looks good but isn’t very comfortable
reviews.reviewText: It is easy to put together and looks great. I switched the wheels out for rubber ones so they wouldn’t scratch the floor but they made the chair look even better. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight ergonomic office chair
reviews.reviewText: I work from home at my kitchen table and often has to get up or move around a bit at the table, so I need a lightweight chair to accommodate that. The assembly itself was quite simple if you follow the picture and the hardware chart, which was labeled so you know exactly what to use at each step. The mesh back rest has the current standard lower back lumbar support that all office chair must have, and it can accommodate my weight with a little springiness. The foam seat cushion is also very soft and breathable, but I like adding the gel pad that I'm used to. Overall I really like this chair, it's not too expensive but it has the necessary feature and comfort that I look for.
